		<hr size="1">I've read over your post and I have to say that, being a wizard myself, I can almost never get into a group.  It seems that shouting "Level 25 wizard, LFG!" Doesn't seem to get many replies, so instead I try to make a group myself.<BR>The toughest with being a wizard is when you are grouped with tank characters who don't need to meditate after every battle who can keep going and going and get annoyed when you shout out, "Please don't kill anything else right now, I need to meditate!" Because otherwise unable to cast, you sometimes feel like dead weight.  Or else you try your hand at tanking, which I have been prone to do quite often. (Well it's fun)</P><P>But I don't think Verant should be scared of soloing wizards because at about level 24, or if you ever go to Kunark, you will die in about 3 or 4 hits from an equal level enemy, and your root spells don't always work.  I do like the idea of a possible mana regeneration bonus, it would keep the tanks happy if we were able to cast more frequently using less time.<BR>But in all honesty wizards do find groups, on the Drinal server groups welcome them quite frequently, it's always handy to have a caster around!<BR><br>&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;<br></font>
	</font>
