		<hr size="1">Ok, I don't play a wizard but I generally like to group with wizards, except when we are fighting high con reds.  That I think, is where you should ask for some sort of balancing.  The other night in S. Karana I was in a full group of low to mid 20's, and we pulled something, I still don't know what, but it exceeded our level by at least six.  All our wizard could do really was thow spit balls at the thing.  Every cast he had was resisted.  I think that Verant needs to do something so that when you're in a group there is some relaxation to the level guided resistants of mobs.</P><P>As far as when to cast and when not too.  The rule I always use is try and keep your mana equal to the primary tanks life.  That way you shouldn't be over burning.  Also the group can see the advantage to having you around if when the primary tank gets in trouble, you suddenly drop 2 big nukes on a mob and save the tanks life.</P><P>Just my 2 cp</P><P>Qwizen level 25 magician of the Rathe<br>&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;<br></font>
