		<hr size="1">Well,</P><P>All I have to say to those of you who can't find groups... there's always someone LFG ... heck.. when someone yells LFG.. i nab that person .. as long as he's no more than 5 levels above myself.  Chances are.. when you shout .. Wiz and so and so need more.. people usually respond..</P><P>I've never had problems finding groups, I'm a generally 'nice' wizard.. and I do solo often.  I solo snarks , gob warlords and charbone skellys in ill omen.. and I always med to 60 before I attack, of course, I'm only level 32, but hey... xp is still good.. </P><P>and there are always druids or shamans near the mill in ill omen, so finding a sow has never been a problem for me.</P><P>when grouped, basically .. all i do is stun a mob, med till stun re-pops.. stun again and lay the smack down with an inferno shock.<BR>by that time, mob is either dead due to the fact that everyone in the group is whacking him/her, or already running with less than a sliver of hp left.  for yellow to red mobs, i throw in a root *knowing that root will break* then throw a snare.. when root breaks.. at least the mob is snared... and when the mob has very little life left and snare is not broken, the mob just stands there waiting to die.  no need to waste mana on something the tanks can kill with 3 or 4 blows.</P><P>and when all else fails... there's this nifty little spell called Shadow Step... use it wisely. then gate to safety.</P><P>safe hunting<br>&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;<br></font>
